{{context|date=December 2016}}
The ordinary '''Bondi–Metzner–Sachs (BMS) group''' B is the common asymptotic [[symmetry group]] of all radiating, [[Asymptotically flat spacetime|asymptotically flat]], Lorentzian [[spacetime]]s. This means that B is currently the best candidate for the universal symmetry group of [[General Relativity]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/1742-6596/33/1/028/meta |title=Generalizations of the BMS group and results}}</ref> It was originally proposed in 1962 by H. Bondi, M. G. van der Burg, and A. W. Metzner.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arxiv.org/pdf/1403.5803.pdf |title=Notes on the BMS group in three dimensions: I. Induced representations}}</ref>

